
# Research

+ Firebase is a good choice for this challenge. Having intergated sms provider.
+ Decied to go with postgres database, Python Flask framework (backend) and vue (Frontend). Since in my recent project I worked on these technologies. Would be save time to research other approaches in 
nodejs or golang.

Day1:

Writing some simple Frontend with Firebase to check the database neccessary for backend. Mostly wanted to check firebase data that we need to keep in database.

Designed database for user management service

Day2:

Designed api view with flask

Day3: 

Developed Docker file,
Automation scipting and testing.


requirements:

docker-compose version 1.25.2
Docker version 19.03.5
Python 3.7.6
psql 12.3

Run:

navigate to :

python3 -m venv venv

source venv/bin/active to active the project

pip install -r requirements

export FLASK_APP=app.py
export APP_SETTINGS=local
export DATABASE_URL="postgresql+psycopg2://postgres:unDG8lDxcvyh9Jl2@localhost:5432/UserManagement"
export FLASK_ENV=development

run flask run


Open another sell



source venv/bin/active to active the project

export FLASK_APP=app.py
export APP_SETTINGS=local
export DATABASE_URL="postgresql+psycopg2://postgres:unDG8lDxcvyh9Jl2@localhost:5432/user_mgr"
export FLASK_ENV=development


in order to check the postgresql

psql "host=127.0.0.1 sslmode=disable dbname=user_mgr user=postgres"

psql -h 127.0.0.1 -p 5432 -U postgres -d user_mgr
